Steps to create a React project using Vite
--------------------------------------------------------
1. Install Node.js
-----------------------
Make sure Node.js is installed:
node -v
npm -v

2. Create a Vite + React project
-----------------------------------------
Run:  
npm create vite@latest

Youâ€™ll be prompted to choose:

Project name
Framework â†’ React
Variant â†’ JavaScript or TypeScript

3. Move into project folder
----------------------------
cd project-name

4. Install dependencies
----------------------------
npm install

5. Start the development server
-----------------------------------
npm run dev

Open the browser at:
----------------------
http://localhost:5173

Note : 
To implement css , link index.css file into index.html and main.jsx 
like this : 
1. html.index : <link rel="stylesheet" href="/my-first-react-project/src/index.css">

2. main.jsx   : import "./index.css";

3. remove default content element from App.jsx and keep only this below like code to write your content 

function App() {
  return (
    <>
       
    </>
  );
}

export default App;

-------------------------------------
Alternative (direct command)
------------------------------------
npm create vite@latest my-react-app -- --template react


Or for TypeScript:

npm create vite@latest my-react-app -- --template react-ts

